{
  "doc_id": "58644",
  "text": "Further applications of microsatellites should be improved by the development of marker-specific allelic ladders to avoid discrepancies in the determination of allele size and to harmonise evaluation of data generated by different equipment and in different laboratories [CITATION_1] . Efficient use of microsatellites should also be increased by the availability of a larger set of new microsatellite markers suitable for multiloading and multiplexing, respectively [CITATION_2] . In addition, microsatellites could be used for genetic uniformity detection in grapevine plants propagated in vitro [CITATION_3] and plant origin certification. Moreover, wine quality control and falsification, respectively, can be analysed from DNA extracted from wine [CITATION_4] . Other DNA markers such as AFLPs, M-AFLPs, SAMPLs, ISSRs, and SNPs [CITATION_5] have also been suggested for studies of genetic variation accumulated over centuries of cultivation and selection in different environments.",
